--- a/docs/man/sesman.ini.5.in
+++ b/docs/man/sesman.ini.5.in
@@ -355,6 +355,27 @@
 This setting will be removed in a later version of xrdp, when GNOME 3 is
 no longer supported.
 
+.TP
+\fBEnablePrinterRedirection\fR=\fI[true|false]\fR
+Defaults to \fItrue\fR.
+Enable or disable RDP printer redirection. When enabled, printers
+announced by the RDP client are made available as CUPS queues in the
+session. Set to \fIfalse\fR to completely disable printer redirection.
+
+.TP
+\fBEnablePerSessionCupsd\fR=\fI[true|false]\fR
+Defaults to \fItrue\fR.
+When \fItrue\fR, each session runs its own private \fBcupsd\fR instance.
+This provides full isolation between users, stable queue names (user
+preferences like paper size persist across sessions), and requires no
+special group membership.
+.P
+.RS
+When set to \fIfalse\fR, redirected printers are created on the system
+\fBcupsd\fR. The session user must be a member of the \fBlpadmin\fR group.
+Queue names include the display number to avoid conflicts between sessions.
+.RE
+
 .SH "SESSIONS VARIABLES"
 All entries in the \fB[SessionVariables]\fR section are set as
 environment variables in the user's session.
